Quoting you: "hardly any bezels" proves my point that there are bezels. In 2019 when other phones are trying for no bezels proves how lazy the designers of Sony are when they would rather aim for the 2018 Note 9 bezels.
And contrary to your accusation, I actually counter-checked it from other sites other than this one. And yes, they all show 2017-2018 bezels for the forthcoming Sony phone.﻿

@Mrwhosetheboss It has an Iris Scanner and actual fingerprint sensor, which is far more secure than the S10's face unlock. And the rear camera is not "a fair bit behind", or whatever that means.

Also, "far bulkier"? Yeah, that's what Note phones are known for. Taller, larger batteries (in this case compared to the S10e/S10), Wacom stylus support. So I'm not really sure how you're able to make such a comparison when the devices are intended for different users.

While you make valid points, like about the CPU being less efficient, a lot of your list is just "the S10+ is newer, so it's better across the board". For example, some people prefer some bezel (which, by the way they are as small as it gets) over a hole/pill in the display.﻿

